			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One of the post here said to try the gargoles on spectre island in Ocean of Tears. Well I tryed it out, died twice lost 3 pets alot of down time. The greater skellies are the place holders for them. Just don't kill too many or you will have more gargoyles then you can handle. You have to melee with your pet to insure victory. Cast fire shield on your self and your pet then blast one from a distance. When the garg comes try to get on one side while your pet is on the other side of him. This way you can tell which one his is agro on you or your pet. If he's on your pet blast him so he doesn't kill your pet then your screwed. Try to melee till you have about half your hitpoints, then back off and let your pet agro him then blast him. I have noticed these guys go right for my pet and try to kill it 1st. Thats why I said get at an angle where you can tell which one he's agro on. Try to keep him to you then your pet over and over again to keep him busy so he doesn't kill you or your pet 1st. Once one or the other happens your toast. Do not use a fire pet. It has the least amount of hit points and these guys hit hard as hec. I used a water pet and put the fire sheild on us both. Now when you kill the skelly's to make the garg's spawn try to only kill 1 or 2. The gargoyles will fight the skelly's making more of the garg's spawn. This is also an advantage to you. If you see them fighting wait till the garg wins then pull him. The skelly takes about 15-20% of his hit points. If mana and health permits pull him right away. This makes it easier on you. They don't have any loot except the garg eyes witch are used for one of your focus items quest from Solesk Ro Temple. These are uncommon since I killed around 8 of these guys and only got 2 eyes. I was thinking the weren't going to drop any till one of them dropped 2 eyes( go figure). <br>After dieing the last time and I had 2 eyes, I decided to come back later when I could handle these bad boys a little better.<br>So I traveled to Timorous deep and went to the island next to Ogre isle and killed Falen Iksar. They were high blue and I could take 2 of them out before I had to med back up.<br>That is currently where I am and I will post more an this later.<br>P.S. I was lvl 18 at the time I was doing this.FYI<br>Narkonus   on Brell Serilis server <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
